  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing the African Unions Mediation Capacity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The African Union&#xE2;&#x80;&#x99;s Conflict Management Division (AU CMD) and the African Centre for the Constructive Resolution of Disputes (ACCORD) ) with the support of Crisis Management Initiative (CMI) will undertake a joint project aimed at building the mediation capacity of the African Union through evidenced-based self-reflection_ the development of an AU mediation strategy and capacity building programming. The partners will study various African mediation case studies_ identify lessons learned and best practises_ generate strategic and operational recommendations_ develop guidelines and procedures_ develop mediation support mechanisms_ conduct training courses and support fact-finding_ mediation_ and post-conflict field missions.</narrative>
  </description>
